    "reasoning": "The specification requires implementing the functionality of a 7420 integrated circuit. The 7420 contains two 4-input NAND gates. The module has two outputs, `p1y` and `p2y`, which correspond to the outputs of these two gates. The inputs are eight single-bit inputs: `p1a`, `p1b`, `p1c`, `p1d` (inputs for the first NAND gate) and `p2a`, `p2b`, `p2c`, `p2d` (inputs for the second NAND gate).\n\n1. **Identify the logic:** A 4-input NAND gate performs the operation: $Y = \neg (A \text{ AND } B \text{ AND } C \text{ AND } D)$.\n2. **Map to module ports:**\n    *   The first NAND gate takes inputs $p1a, p1b, p1c, p1d$ and produces output $p1y$.\n    *   The second NAND gate takes inputs $p2a, p2b, p2c, p2d$ and produces output $p2y$.\n3. **Implement NAND gate in SystemVerilog:** The NAND operation is equivalent to an AND operation followed by a NOT, or using the bitwise NOT operator (`~`) on the AND result (`&`).\n    *   $p1y = \text{NOT} (p1a \text{ AND } p1b \text{ AND } p1c \text{ AND } p1d) \rightarrow p1y = ~(p1a & p1b & p1c & p1d)$\n    *   $p2y = \text{NOT} (p2a \text{ AND } p2b \text{ AND } p2c \text{ AND } p2d) \rightarrow p2y = ~(p2a & p2b & p2c & p2d)$\n4. **Structure:** Since the operation is purely combinational, continuous `assign` statements are the most efficient and idiomatic way to implement this.\n5. **Syntax Advice:** Ensure all signals are declared as `logic`. Use the correct operators (`&` for AND, `~` for NOT) for the NAND function. The interface must exactly match the provided specification, which it does.",
    "module": "module TopModule (\n    input  logic p1a,\n    input  logic p1b,\n    input  logic p1c,\n    input  logic p1d,\n    input  logic p2a,\n    input  logic p2b,\n    input  logic p2c,\n    input  logic p2d,\n    output logic p1y,\n    output logic p2y\n);\n\n    // Implementation of the first 4-input NAND gate (7420 part 1)\n    // Y = NOT (A AND B AND C AND D)\n    assign p1y = ~(p1a & p1b & p1c & p1d);\n\n    // Implementation of the second 4-input NAND gate (7420 part 2)\n    // Y = NOT (A AND B AND C AND D)\n    assign p2y = ~(p2a & p2b & p2c & p2d);\n\nendmodule"
